Modification of '16. Limitation of Liability' which can be found in the file COPYING (GPL).

Claims for damages are excluded, unless they are based on intent or gross negligence.
In the case of gross negligence, liability for indirect and consequential damages is excluded.
The exclusions and limitations do not apply to claims under the Product Liability Act, due to fraudulent behavior, from liability for guaranteed 
characteristics and from injury to life, limb or health.
